kontinu
=======

Typed JavaScript library to create endless scroll with no
third-party dependency nor Web API involed.

Quick Start
-----------

Required dependencies:

    - TypeScript transpiler (tsc, swc)

Usage
-----

Simply invoke the function __init():

    kontinu.__init(element.querySelector("#start"), (element: HTMLElement): HTMLElement => {
        const newElement = document.createElement("div");
        newElement.style = "width: 50px; height: 50px; background-color: blue";
        element.insertAdjacentElement("afterend", newElement)); 
        return newElement;
    });

The function above requires you to pass a starting element, this
case I pass an empty div with the id of #start.

It also requires a function callback on intersection which
should append and return the new element.
